{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01WL1RdaKK58Dg55hiuTsejq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01LToNEPfKvKocFJQdTakKS4","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Catching the real failure (embedding model API changes its output dimension, incompatible with the index) requires calling the actual embedding service API. A mocked embedding model could return any dimension without revealing dimension mismatches or API incompatibilities. The integration between embedding output and vector database schema can only be verified by calling the real embedding API.","test_description":"Call the real embedding API with a sample query string and verify the returned vector has exactly N dimensions (where N matches the vector database index schema). Optionally, attempt to insert the vector into the actual vector database to confirm structural compatibility. Repeat with multiple query formats to ensure consistency.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test correctly targets System level: requires real external embedding API call.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.85,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A mock vector database could always return results in the correct order, hiding real bugs in the database's ordering or our code's handling of the results. The real failure is that the vector database returns results in wrong order or our sorting logic is broken. This requires querying an actual (or test) vector database instance with known vectors and similarity scores.","test_description":"Populate a test vect