n":"A query with no close matches in the database returns an empty result set rather than low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A mock database could always return empty results, hiding threshold-filtering bugs. The real failure is that the system returns low-similarity results instead of filtering them out. Testing requires a real (test) vector database populated with known vectors, queried with unrelated terms, and verifying the similarity threshold correctly filters out low-match results.","test_description":"Populate a test vector database with domain-specific vectors (e.g., electronics products). Query with an unrelated string (e.g., 'pasta recipes'). Verify that with a similarity threshold (e.g., 0.5), the result set is empty. Test boundary conditions: set threshold to 0.99 and verify results remain empty; lower threshold below the maximum similarity score and verify results reappear. Confirm threshold filtering works consistently across multiple unrelated queries.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test correctly targets Integration level: requires real vector database with threshold logic, not mocked.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The end-to-end latency from receiving the query to returning re-ranked results stays below 2 seconds for the median case.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Latency bottlenecks only appear when all real components (embedding API, vector database, LLM re-ranker) operate together. Mocked embeddings and LLMs would not reveal network delays, database query time, or LLM inference latency. The real failure is the production pipeline exceeds 2 seconds. Testing requires orchestrating multiple agentic/infrastructure steps in sequence, measuring true end-to-end latency across realistic queries.","test_description":"Send natural language queries (e.g., 'durable water bottles under $30') through the entire pipeline: embedding generation → vector database similarity search → LLM re-ranking. Measure elapsed time from API request receipt to response delivery. Run at least 10 iterations with diverse queries to account for LLM non-determinism and variable latency. Verify median latency is below 2 seconds and document the 95th percentile.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test correctly targets Workflow level: requires full multi-step pipeline with real embedding, vector DB, and LLM components.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.8}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13530,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13530},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"979af25e-f78c-47df-865b-67c6c878de8e","uuid":"111e1491-a9f5-4f09-bcc3-9ac878bdc026"}
